The Targets were Highly Enriched Self-Supporting Foils
Having a Thickness of 0.87 mg/cm**2 For Zn-92 and
0.92 mg/cm**2 For Zr-94.
For the Calculation of the Inelastic Cross Sections the
Enrichments were Assumed to be the Highest Available
From Oak Ridge,Namely 95.7% For Zr-92 and 97.9% For
.Optical Model Analysis For Elastic Cross Section
And Distorted-Wave Theory For the Inelastic Angular
Distributions.
.A Single Silicon Surface-Barrier Detector with
An Area of 0.5 cm**2 was Placed at a Distance of 5.85-
Inchs from Target.
